> We've put together all the fixins for a full-on barbecue feast: sticky baby back
> ribs, juicy chicken cutlets, and a side of cornbread. Grill up the ribs and
> chicken or cook on the stovetop—either way, you'll have your bbq fix in no time.

== Ribs ==

Remove @BBQ Baby Back Ribs{24%ounce} from package, reserving any extra sauce.
Place on a lightly-oiled piece of #foil{} large enough to wrap around ribs.
Brush tops of ribs with remaining sauce. Tightly crimp foil to form a packet.

Grill: Place foil packet on #grill grates{}; close #grill{}. Cook until ribs are
warmed through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Oven: Place foil packet on a #baking sheet{}. Bake until ribs are warmed
through and edges are lightly caramelized, ~{22-25%minutes}.

Remove ribs from packet. Cut between bones into desired number of portions and
drizzle with sauce from foil packet.

== Chicken ==

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{20%ounce} dry and season generously with @salt{} and
@pepper{} (or your favorite spices).

Grill: Grill on oiled grates until browned and cooked through (we suggest
~{3-5%minutes} per side, but grills can vary!).

Stovetop: Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over
medium-high heat. Cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per
side.

Let rest a few minutes, then slice.

== Cornbread ==

Heat #oven{} to 375 degrees. Separate @Cornbread Swirls{11%ounce} into 6 rounds
(do not unroll). Place each roll into a greased #muffin cup{}.

Bake for ~{13-17%minutes}, or until golden brown. Serve warm or bake ahead and
reheat briefly in the #microwave{}.